{
  "stem": "521.4",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "Soup which one where there was a floating all sorts of things among other maybe a piece of noodle or two, and that was keeping us alive, plus one slice of bread, one solitary slice with water.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "We have, of course-- it was prepared by the kitchen.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "Now the people who were working in the kitchen, they had other food to eat.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "Only thing is that didn't get down to us.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "Now the people who were in the kitchen were Jews.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "Now, of course, the Jews were keeping the food, a good part of the food for themselves because they were very well fed, and we were getting slimmer and slimmer.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "It had an advantage.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "There were some people who were diabetic, very, very-- well, and they were worried what is going to happen to them when their insulin, or whatever preparation they were taking, is going to run out.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "They didn't have to worry about it.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "The diabetics became as same as anybody because the minute they lost the weight, they lost the cholesterol, they lost everything what causes diabetic.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "And when they have returned, whoever returned to Hungary, they were healthy until they started to eat again.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "So there were some people who are benefiting by being in a concentration camp.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "Now the worst thing was when somebody got diarrhea.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "Once you got the diarrhea, you died because there was nothing to stop the diarrhea.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "There were some doctors with us who have taken bones.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "You know, the kitchen had bones.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 45,
      "text": "So if the kitchen had bones, they must have had some meat on the bones, but we never got the meat part of the bones.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 46,
      "text": "They were burnt to coal.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
